According to BP 2105, on or before May 15 of each year, the Board shall consider whether to afford the student members any of the following privileges:
		 
The privilege to make and second motions;
The privilege to attend closed sessions, other than closed sessions on personnel or collective bargaining matters;
The privilege to receive compensation for meeting attendance at a level of $221 or 50% of the regular Board Member compensation for any given month See BP 2725;
The privilege to serve a term commencing on May 15;
The privilege to cast an advisory vote although the vote shall not be included in determining the vote required to approve any measure before the Board.
		 
On an annual basis, the Board of Trustees has approved all of the above privileges for Student Trustees, with the exception of the privilege to attend Closed Session meetings. It is, therefore, recommended that the Board of Trustees continue with its practice of approving all the privileges outlined in BP 2105, with the exception of the privilege to attend Closed Session meetings.
